data.name: lblMultiDesc.Text
data.value:
If your game spans multiple hex files, the 'Game Prefix' and 'Game Sequence' are stored in the EEPROM to ensure that the HEX files are played and completed in sequence.
The 'Game Prefix' is just a unique number that is common to all of the levels in your game. Select a value between 0 - 255 and ensure that all other HEX files in this game use the same value.
The 'Game Sequence' specifies the sequence that this HEX file is within the game set. Start at 1 and ensure each game has an incrementing value.
